    "category": "Reproductive Endocrinology - Disorders of Sex Development",
    "question": "A 46,XX newborn presents with ambiguous genitalia at birth. The mother reports experiencing significant acne, deepening of her voice, and facial hair growth during the latter half of the pregnancy, which resolved postpartum. The infant has normal blood pressure and normal serum electrolytes. Which of the following is the most likely underlying defect?",
