    "explanation": "The patient has lipoid congenital adrenal hyperplasia, primarily caused by mutations in the StAR (Steroidogenic Acute Regulatory) protein. StAR is responsible for transporting cholesterol from the outer to the inner mitochondrial membrane, the rate-limiting step in all steroidogenesis. Without it, adrenals and gonads fail to produce any steroids, leading to salt wasting, phenotypically female genitalia in 46,XY individuals, and massive adrenal lipid accumulation. P450scc (side-chain cleavage) mutations are less common and typically do not present with massively enlarged adrenals."
