    "explanation": "The two-cell, two-gonadotropin theory posits that LH binds to LH receptors on theca cells, activating cholesterol desmolase to produce androgens (mostly androstenedione). These androgens diffuse across the basement membrane into the avascular granulosa cell layer. FSH binds to FSH receptors on granulosa cells, upregulating the enzyme aromatase (CYP19A1), which converts the theca-derived androstenedione into estradiol."
