    "question": "Follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) synthesis and secretion are tightly regulated by several circulating factors. Among these, the gonadal peptide Activin plays a critical paracrine and endocrine role. Which of the following best describes the intracellular signaling mechanism by which Activin exerts its effect on the anterior pituitary gonadotropes?",
