    "question": "A 40-year-old trauma patient develops profound hypoxemia (PaO2 45 mmHg) while breathing room air. Calculation reveals a significantly widened alveolar-arterial (A-a) oxygen gradient. The patient is placed on 100% supplemental oxygen via a non-rebreather mask, but a repeat arterial blood gas reveals a PaO2 that remains critically low at 55 mmHg. Which of the following mechanisms is the predominant cause of this patient's hypoxemia?",
