    "explanation": "Hypoxemia with a widened A-a gradient that fails to correct with 100% oxygen is the hallmark of a right-to-left absolute shunt (V/Q = 0). Since the shunted blood entirely bypasses ventilated alveoli, increasing alveolar PO2 in the healthy lung units cannot compensate for the deeply deoxygenated admixed blood."
